1.Remove react-icons package
2.Use styled-icon instead of react-icons (Styled icons are tree shakable) https://styled-icons.de
3.Add a new generic table components using react-virtualized
Please check : https://openbase.com/js/react-virtualized
4.Style the tables using tailwind css (you can use the code in this link
https://tailwindui.com/components/application-ui/lists/tables) (First table)
5.Migrate the generic components created to the component folder
6.Migrate the next project to typescript and transform all file to .tsx

NB: Before choosing any package to browse https://openbase.com/categories/js
so you can have a look on available packages that can help you achieve your goal.
Always look for packages that support tree-sharking and have support for typescript
and packages that hasn't been deprecated

Other : Learn about the concept of tree-shaking so you can understand the importance
of picking the right library for the job while making sure of the performance


